alent Dose taken before going to bed.</p><p><italic>SSRI</italic>, selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors.</p><p><italic>TCA,</italic> tricyclic antidepressants.</p><p>Bold p values are significant.</p></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap></sec><sec><title>Sleep parameters</title><p>Objective sleep quality in PD + RBD patients was lower; patients with RBD spent more time awake, and had a shorter total sleep time and lower sleep efficiency (Table&#x000a0;<xref ref-type="table" rid="T3">3</xref>). The prevalence of sleep disorders other than RBD was not different between groups (Table&#x000a0;<xref ref-type="table" rid="T3">3</xref>).</p><table-wrap position="float" id="T3"><label>Table 3</label><caption><p>Sleep parameters</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups" border="1"><colgroup><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/></colgroup><thead valign="top"><tr><th align="left">&#x000a0;</th><th align="left"><bold>RBD+</bold></th><th align="left"><bold>RBD-</bold></th><th align="left"><bold>p</bold></th></tr></thead><tbody valign="top"><tr><td align="left" valign="bottom">N<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">23<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">22<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">&#x000a0;<hr/></td></tr><tr><td align="left" valign="bottom"><bold>PSG results</bold><hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">&#x000a0;<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">&#x000a0;<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">&#x000a0;<hr/></td></tr><tr><td align="left" valign="bottom">Total sleep time (min)<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">330.0&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;51.6<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom">375.6&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;65.9<hr/></td><td align="left" valign="bottom"><bold>
